data.name: Farm Management Deposit account
data.description: As a primary producer, invest pre-tax income from high yield years to provide a cash reserve for the future.

features.additionalInfo: Deposits into the account may be deducted from your assessable income in the year of deposit if it complies with Farm Management Scheme Deposit Requirements and elegibility
Saves money securely away for when you need it
Pays guaranteed returns with a fixed interest rate
Could earn higher interest than a standard savings account.

eligibility.additionalInfo: You must be an individual primary producer in Australia earning no more than $100,000 p.a. in non-farm income in the year of the FMD deposit

eligibility.additionalValue: You must be operating as a sole trade, partner in a partnership or beneficiary of a trust

eligibility.additionalInfo: You can have multiple FMD accounts and with different banks, but you cannot hold more than $800,000 in total in FMDs
You must comply with the ATO Farm Management Deposits Scheme special legislative requirements.
